OL,4,C'impunity', inquiry told
OL,6,FSimon McLarnon described how he
OL,7,Fattempted to help victims of the
OL,8,Fexplosion, but was left with a
OL,9,Flifelong sense of guilt that he was
OL,10,Funable to do more.
OL,12,FMr McLarnon, who works as a general
OL,13,Fdental surgeon in Co Donegal, was at
OL,14,Fhis girlfriend's house in the Co
OL,15,FTyrone town on the day of the blast.
OL,17,FHe told the Omagh Bombing Inquiry: "I
OL,18,Fhad first aid training because I was a
OL,19,Frecent graduate, but I wasn't able to
OL,20,Fuse it on the day.
